y of this seminal figure provides a revealing insight into British and European music and concert life during the long nineteenth century. CHRISTOPHER FIFIELD is a conductor, music historian, lecturer and broadcaster.He is the editor and author of the Letters and Diaries of Kathleen Ferrier and Max Bruch: His Life and Works, both published in new editions by The Boydell Press. He has also written Ibbs & Tillett - The rise andfall of a Musical Empire and The German Symphony between Beethoven and Brahms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aConductors (Music)zGermanyvBiography. 4aMusic. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Composers & Musicians.2bisacsh  aBritish classical music.  aHans Richter.  abiography.  acase study.  afamous conductors.  amemoir.  amusic composition.  amusic performance.  amusic theory.  amusicology.  anineteenth century music.  atwentieth century music.1 aSolti, Sir Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311143131440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178204823740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782048237423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782048237/original  a978-3-11-143131-4  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles